CONTAINING;


I. An Account of the Riches, Strength, Magnificence, Natural Production, Manufactures of this Iſland, with an exact Catalogue of the Nobility, and their Seats, &c.


II. The Trade and Commerce within it ſelf, and with all Countries traded to by the Engliſh, as at this day eſtabliſhed, and all other Matters relating to Inland and Marine Affairs.
